# Push after changes

When you finish making code or content changes in this portfolio repo:

1. Run `git status` / `git diff` to see what changed.
2. Commit with a clear message (only when there are real changes).
3. Push to `origin main` (`git push origin main`).

Do this by default after completing a task — the user wants GitHub (and Vercel) kept up to date. Do not force-push. Do not commit secrets (`.env.local`, API keys).
